<p>While localizing the Content for an ASPX page through Visual studio and selecting the Option: "Generate Local Resources " the text is not getting localized for all HTMLs. FOr example, There are <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tags and other server control tags like Label.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;Carrying out Localization on my First Website &lt;/p&gt; &lt;asp:Label runat="server" ID="label1"&gt;&lt;/asp:label&gt; </code></pre>  <p>After selecting the Option: "Generate Local Resources " from "Tools" menu, below is what seen in markup: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;Carrying out Localization on my First Website &lt;/p&gt; &lt;asp:Label runat="server" ID="label1" meta:resourcekey="labelResource1"&gt;&lt;/asp:label&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I localize the content placed inside <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tags or any <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code> tags ?</p>